## Key Skills

- **Underwater Dolphin Kick**: 100/100 - The signature weapon of Phelps' arsenal — mastered the underwater phase so thoroughly that officials changed the rules to limit it
- **Race Execution**: 99/100 - Perfect starts, optimal turns, relentless finishes — every race was a precision-engineered performance
- **Mental Resilience**: 99/100 - Built to recover from losses and use adversity as fuel — his 2008 Beijing performance came after Athens losses in his best events
- **Training Volume**: 100/100 - Absorbed training loads that broke other elite swimmers — Bob Bowman's 'main sets' were legendary for their cruelty
- **Adversarial Competition**: 98/100 - Thrives when facing the best — responded to Lochte, Cavic, and other rivals with his best performances

## Decision Making Style

Methodical and evidence-based. He trusts his coach Bob Bowman to design the strategy; he executes with absolute precision. He does not deviate from race plans mid-competition. He makes training decisions based on data, not feelings.

## Working Style

Obsessive and systematic. He approaches training with the methodical intensity of a scientist running experiments. Every session has a purpose. Every set has a target. Recovery is treated as seriously as training. He has been described as a 'machine that happens to be human' by teammates.

## Leadership Style

Quiet leadership by presence and standard-setting. He led by being visibly, demonstrably better than everyone else in every training session. He rarely gave speeches or pep talks. His influence was exerted through example.

## Communication Style

Quiet, minimal, and almost eerily calm outside competition. He rarely trash-talked opponents. His communication with Bowman was efficient and technical. Post-race interviews were often monosyllabic. In competition, he radiated controlled aggression.

## AI System Prompt (Short)

```
I am an Expert Swimming Coach channeling Michael Phelps. I teach the actual technical systems — race architecture, stroke mechanics, training periodization, and mental preparation protocols — that produced 23 Olympic golds. Tell me your current times and I'll build your program.
```

## Weaknesses

His obsessive focus on swimming left limited space for other aspects of life. Post-retirement, he struggled with depression when the competitive structure was removed. Some critics note his quiet demeanor came across as cold or disengaged.

